FR940504-0-00029 FR940504-0-00009 List of Subjects in 40 CFR Part 52 Environmental protection, Air pollution control, Hydrocarbons, Incorporation by reference, Intergovernmental relations, Ozone. Note: Incorporation by reference of the State Implementation Plan for the State of Ohio was approved by the Director of the Federal Register on July 1, 1982. Dated: April 13, 1994. Carol M. Browner, Administrator. Part 52, chapter I, title 40 of the Code of Federal Regulations is amended as follows: PART 52_APPROVAL AND PROMULGATION OF IMPLEMENTATION PLANS 1. The authority citation for part 52 continues to read as follows: Authority: 42 U.S.C. 7401&hyph;7671q. Subpart KK_Ohio 2. Section 52.1870 is amended by adding paragraph (c)(90) to read as follows: §52.1870 Identification of plan. * * * * * (c) *␣*␣* (90) On April 9, 1986, the Ohio Environmental Protection Agency (OEPA) submitted amendments to the Ohio Administrative Code (OAC) Chapter 3745&hyph;21. The amendments are embodied in the following OAC regulations: Definitions, Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;01; Attainment dates and compliance time schedules, Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;04; Control of emissions of volatile organic compounds from stationary sources, Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09; and Compliance test methods and procedures, Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;10. USEPA is approving these amendments with the following exceptions: The proposed relaxation for food can end sealing compounds in 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(D)(1)(e) and (D)(2)(e) (from 3.7 to 4.4 lbs VOC/gallon); the proposed revision to the exemption in 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(N)(3)(e) for the application by hand of any cutback asphalt or emulsified asphalt for patching or crack sealing; the recordkeeping requirements in 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(N)(4); the relaxation from 3.5 to 6.2 lbs VOC/gallon for high performance architectural aluminum coatings in 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(U)(1)(a)(viii); the exemption for new sources in 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(U)(2)(f); and the relaxation for miscellaneous metals coatings in 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(U)(1)(a)(vii). (i) Incorporation by reference. (A) Amendments to Ohio Administrative Code Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;01, effective on May 9, 1986. (B) Amendments to Ohio Administrative Code Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;04, effective on May 9, 1986. (C) Amendments to Ohio Administrative Code Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09, effective on May 9, 1986, except for: (1) 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(D)(1)(e) and (D)(2)(e) (proposed relaxation for food can end sealing); (2) 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(N)(3)(e) (proposed revision to the exemption for the application by hand of any cutback or emulsified asphalt for patching crack sealing); (3) 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(N)(4) (recordkeeping requirements); (4) 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(U)(1)(a)(viii) (relaxation from 3.5 to 6.2 lbs VOC. gal for high performance architectural aluminum coatings); (5) 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(U)(2)(f) (the exemption for new sources); and (6) 3745&hyph;21&hyph;09(U)(1)(a)(vii) (relaxation for miscellaneous metal coatings). (D) Amendments to Ohio Administrative Code Rule 3745&hyph;21&hyph;10, effective May 9, 1996. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;10652 Filed 5&hyph;3&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 6580&hyph;50&hyph;P
